snippet: At least 17 people were killed by three bombs and a grenade attack on a mosque in Baghdad on Monday, medics and the police said.
abstract: At least 17 people were killed and 33 people wounded, including several Sunni Muslim worshipers and police officers, in three bomb attacks in Baghdad, Iraq.
lead_paragraph: At least 17 people were killed by three bombs and a grenade attack on a mosque in Baghdad on Monday, medics and the police said.

headline.seo: Iraq: At Least 17 People Killed in Baghdad Attacks
